The paper deals with the problem of minimizing deterministic finite automata, which is a topic in formal languages (cs.FL) and data structures (cs.DS). The algorithms used in the paper involve techniques from computational geometry and linear algebra, which are also relevant to discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The paper also discusses experimental results, which suggests that machine learning (cs.LG) and complexity theory (cs.CC) may be relevant as well.
